OL,3,C#15bn Covid contracts raise 'profound'
OL,4,Ccorruption concerns, campaigners say
OL,6,FResearch of Covid-related contracts
OL,7,Fworth about #15.5 billion has prompted
OL,8,F"profound" concerns about corruption,
OL,9,Faccording to campaigners.
OL,11,FThe analysis, conducted by
OL,12,FTransparency International UK,
OL,13,Fquestioned the nature of 135 contracts
OL,14,Fmade during the pandemic.
OL,16,FThe group points to at least 28
OL,17,Fcontracts, worth #4.1 billion, which
OL,18,Fwent to organisations with close
OL,19,Fconnections at Westminster,
OL,20,Fparticularly with the then
OL,21,FConservative government.
